Kim Yong Nam Meets UNESCO Director-General and His Party 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly talk with Koitsiro Matsuura, director-general of the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), and his party at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand was Pak Kil Yon, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Director-General of UNESCO 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by Koitsiro Matsuura, director-general of the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, by Koitsiro Matsuura on September 12.

Myanmar Friendship Delegation Here 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- A friendship delegation of Myanmar headed by Aung Thein Lynn, mayor of Yangon City and chairman of Yangon City Development Committee, arrived in Pyongyang on Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The delegation was greeted at the airport by Jon Yong Jin, vice-chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries who is chairman of the DPRK-Myanmar Friendship Association.

Foreigners Visit Pyongyang Mission of AINDF 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Alejandro Cao de Benos, chairman of the Korean Friendship Association headquartered in Spain, and his party visited the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front (AINDF) on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Staff members of the mission including its Chief Jo Il Min had a friendly talk with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They informed each other of activities of their organizations and exchanged views on boosting the relations between the two organizations and a series of matters of common concern.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jo deeply thanked the association for having extended full support to the AINDF and the south Korean people in their just struggles for driving the U.S. forces out of south Korea and reunifying the country in the past period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He referred to the U.S. hostile policy towards the DPRK and its war maneuvers and the anti-U.S., anti-government actions of the south Korean people opposed to the Lee Myung Bak group's sycophancy towards the U.S. and its moves against reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Alejandro Cao de Benos said that the U.S. and the Lee group are leaving no means untried in their moves to bring back the inter-Korean relations to those of confrontation but the Korean people remain unshakable in their will to thoroughly implement the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He declared that the Korean Friendship Association would intensify the movement supporting the patriotic cause of the AINDF and the south Korean people for independence against the U.S. and for national reunification in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day the chairman of the association and his party released a statement denouncing the Lee group's recent suppression of democratic forces in south Korea.

Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Show Closes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia show for celebrating the 60th birthday of the DPRK was closed with due ceremony at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition on Friday. The show drew a large number of servicepersons, people, school youth and children and overseas compatriots and foreign friends every day since it was opened on Sept. 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the closing ceremony were Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop and others, and officials of armed forces organs, ministries, national institutions, working people's organizations and enterprises, servicepersons, working people and members of the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Diplomas of top prize of the show were awarded to seven units and those of prize to 15 units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Diplomas of special prize went to the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan and the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Greenhouse in Hunchun of China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Pyong Hun, chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of the Unions of Literature and the Arts of Korea, made an address at the ceremony.

Events of Agricultural Workers Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The 7th National Games of Agricultural Workers and the 5th National Peasant Dance Contest of Agricultural Workers were held here from Sept. 8 to 11 to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These events were preceded by games and contest held among cooperative farms. The events brought together at least 800 agricultural workers selected in preliminary games and contests held in every city, county and province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the games fully displayed their sports technique and special skills, noble team spirit and traits of fair play they have cultivated after their worthwhile labor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Sinam Cooperative Farm, Ryongchon County in North Phyongan Province, came first in Korean wrestling, swinging and seesaw games, the Osong Cooperative Farm, Jongju City in North Phyongan Province, in Taekwon-Do game, the Mangyongdae Irrigation Management Office in Pyongyang in Korean chess game and the Munam Cooperative Farm, Musan County in North Hamgyong Province, in Yut game. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 North Phyongan Province placed first in team standing.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Hwasong Cooperative Farm, Ryongsong District in Pyongyang, and the Puchang Cooperative Farm, Sinpho City in South Hamgyong Province, and other cooperative farms proved successful in the peasant dance contest by presenting cheerful melody, tune and peculiar rhythms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing ceremony was held at Kim Il Sung Stadium on September 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kang Chang Uk, chairman of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea, Pak Hak Son, chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, and others.

Sports Contest for Celebrating 60th Birthday of DPRK Closed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The sports contest for celebrating the 60th birthday of the DPRK came to a close after being opened on September 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the contest there were football games by players of sports groups and basketball games by officials of ministries and national institutions and other sports events at the Kim Il Sung Stadium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its closing ceremony took place at the Basketball Gymnasium in Chongchun Street here on Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea, and leading officials of working people's organizations, officials of ministries and national institutions, sportspersons and working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Hak Son, chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, made an address at the ceremony.

Letter to Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a letter on Friday by the participants of the joint TV meeting held to mark the 60th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter extended sincere thanks to Kim Jong Il for providing them with opportunities to participate in celebrations of the 60th birthday of the DPRK such as the joint TV meeting and the exhibition of books on the greatness of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and works representing the reverence for them held in Pyongyang, fathoming their earnest desire to join the Korean people in celebrating the significant holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a sacred duty and obligation for us to join the Korean people in significantly celebrating the diamond jubilee of the DPRK as we have always expressed positive support to socialist Korea, a dignified fortress of independence, peace and justice, and written articles to convey the personality of the three generals of Mt. Paektu as great persons and their undying exploits down to posterity, the letter noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are of the view that the celebration events offered significant occasions of demonstrating the desire of progressive mankind to hand the immortal exploits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu, the peerlessly great persons, down to the generations to come and invariably support the Korean people in their just cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will make all efforts to support Songun Korea in the future, too, entrusting the future of the human cause of independence to you just as we have conducted our activities as ardent adherents to the great idea of His Excellency President Kim Il Sung, attracted by his personality as a great man, and positive supporters to the Korean people in their just cause in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter reiterated their resolution to positively support with might and main the Korean people in their heroic struggle to glorify the centenary of birth of Kim Il Sung as the most auspicious event common to humankind in history and fling open the gate of a great prosperous powerful nation without fail.

Sanatoria and Rest Homes Full of Happiness
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Working people are enjoying their holidays in sanatoria and rest homes built in scenic spots of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Han Myong Son, a department director of the Ministry of Labour, told KCNA: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary Kim Jong Il saw to it that steps were taken to develop the social insurance system and accommodation at health resorts and holiday homes so as to provide full conditions for the promotion of the health of the working people and for their cultural recreation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years sanatoria and rest homes have made their appearance in picturesque places in Pongsan, Orang, Jaeryong, Rinsan, Thosan, Suan, Sinphyong and other parts of the country. Conspicuous among them is the well-furnished Hamju County Farmers' Rest Home built at the foot of a mountain near the Kumjingang Hungbong Youth Power Station. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of holiday-makers are enjoying hot spring and sea bathing and colorful cultural amusement games in the Onpho Rest Home constructed to meet the requirements of the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people have come to the newly-reconstructed Myohyangsan Rest Home from different parts of the country. They are spending their holidays to their heart's content, visiting the International Friendship Exhibition and historic sites and climbing Mt. Myohyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Sokam, Songdan, Sokdamgugok and other rest homes have also excellent cultural recreation conditions. They are well organizing daily routine so that the holiday makers may train their soul and body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having keenly felt the benefit of the generous socialist system through their pleasant recreation life, the working people are renewing their mind to strive harder for the prosperity of the country.

U.S. Troops in South Korea, Murderers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Sixty-three years have elapsed since the U.S. imperialists occupied south Korea in September 1945. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The days of the presence of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces in south Korea are a history of blood and shocking crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ever since they set foot in south Korea, the U.S. imperialists have inflicted all manner of immeasurable misfortunes and disasters upon the people there and killed innocent people at random. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They brutally put down the struggle of the people in different parts of south Korea against the U.S. "military government" in October 1946 by setting in motion planes, tanks and chemical weapons, leaving more than 25,000 people dead. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the April 3 Popular Uprising against the May 10 separate election in Jeju Island which continued till June 1949 they also slaughtered over 70,000 out of 300,000 islanders by the most brutal methods. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In five years since the occupation of south Korea by the U.S. imperialists, peaceable inhabitants killed by them totaled over a million. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The atrocious massacres against south Koreans by the U.S. imperialist aggression troops continued even in the postwar days, to say nothing of the period of the Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The endless list of cases of brutal murders committed by the U.S. imperialists includes the shooting of a girl in Kunsan in 1957, the throwing of a boy in a box from a helicopter in Puphyong in February 1958, the shooting of a firewood collector in Phaju in 1962 and a random firing in June 1981. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The murder committed by them in south Korea reached the peak of hysteria during the Kwangju Popular Uprising in May 1980. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the order of the U.S. imperialists the Chun Doo Hwan group killed more than 5,700 inhabitants of all strata and inflicted light and heavy wounds on 14,000 others in a matter of a few days of the popular uprising in Kwangju. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The brutal murder and crimes of the U.S. imperialist aggression troops in south Korea have never ceased in the new century. The typical case is that they ran an armored car over two young middle school girls, Sin Hyo Sun and Sim Mi Son, on a road in Yangju County, Kyonggi Province in broad daylight on June 13, 2002. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States must withdraw its forces from south Korea at once, putting an end to the history of crimes in which it has only imposed misfortunes and sufferings on the south Koreans.

Withdrawal of U.S. Troops from S. Korea Demanded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification released a statement titled "U.S. troops, quit this land at once" on September 8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that Sept. 8 is the day of disgrace which marks the lapse of 63 years since the U.S. troops occupied south Korea, strongly demanding the U.S. troops, a hotbed of plunder and crimes and a nuclear war, quit south Korea at once. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though 63 years have passed since their occupation of this land they remain unchanged in their aggressive and predatory nature, the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. forces are busy staging war exercises for aggression under an undisguised war scenario for mounting a preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK, threatening the existence of the nation, the statement noted, urging the U.S. troops in south Korea to give up all the policies of war on the Korean Peninsula and their hostile policy towards the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Should the U.S. and sycophantic and traitorous forces continue to pursue a policy of war and subjugation in disregard of the trend of the times and the great cause of the people, they will have to pay a dear price for the crimes they have committed in this land, it warned.

Japan's Revision of "Law on Special Measures against Terrorism" Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, the chief executive of Japan met with the U.S. president and promised that Japan's Maritime "Self-Defence Force" would carry on its refueling action in the Indian Ocean. Then, he had a confidential talk with Japan's defence minister over the matter of submitting to the provisional Diet a new "amendment to the law on special measures against terrorism". He also instructed the minister to give the people understandable explanation about the "importance" of Japan's involvement in the "anti-terrorism war".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The defence minister and the foreign minister of Japan, too, stressed the "need" to revise the above-said law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on it, a news analyst of Rodong Sinmun today charges that their assertion is intended to let the "Self-Defence Forces" go on their advance and operational activities overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ulterior intention of the Japanese reactionaries, who persist in the revision of the law while leaving no stones unturned to carry it into practice, is to always act a war servant for the U.S and set out on the road of overseas expansion with the backing of their master obtained in return for their service, the commentary points out, and says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their theory of revising the law precisely means a doctrine for overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are advertising about the opinion of the world community as if it is expressing "understanding" and "sympathy" with their involvement in the "anti-terrorism war". Such behavior is nothing but a distortion of the reality and a foolish deed of those not knowing where they stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world community does never want the Japanese militarists to participate and make "contribution" to the U.S.-led "anti-terrorism war" which makes blood-stained history of aggression. On the contrary, it demands that Japan settle its crime-woven past as early as possible and immediately stop the moves for overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries had better behave themselves, facing up to the trend of the times.

Lee Myung Bak Group's Suppression Condemned
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Members of the Korean Friendship Association headquartered in Spain and its Thai and German branches released a statement in Pyongyang Thursday denouncing the Lee Myung Bak group's suppression of the democratic forces in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing the Lee group of taking such fascist action as inflicting a heavy penalty upon Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification, on the charge of the violation of the ill-famed "National Security Law" in the wake of arresting and detaining leading members of the Solidarity for Progress in south Korea and workers there one after another, the statement went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group's indiscriminate racket of suppression and hideous gangsterism have turned south Korea into a dark land of fascism and a tundra of human rights, a land swept by a whirlwind of harsh suppression reminiscent of military dictatorship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We bitterly condemn the Lee group's crackdown upon the democratic forces as a wanton infringement upon justice, democracy and human rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No matter how desperately the present south Korean ruling quarters try to tide over their ruling crisis through their merciless suppression, they can never quell the indomitable fighting spirit of the south Korean people nor can they break their will nor can they block their advance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group will not escape the people's curse and denunciation but meet self-destruction, should they continue resorting to fascism and dictatorship, instead of drawing a lesson from the miserable end met by the erstwhile dictatorial forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement demanded the Lee Myung Bak group repeal the NSL, an undemocratic and anti-reunification law, unconditionally release the unreasonably detained progressive figures and participants in candlelight actions and immediately stop their suppression of the south Korean people in their just struggle for the right to existence and democracy.

War Moves of U.S. and S. Korea against DPRK Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The chairman of the Pretoria Branch of the Democratic Teachers' Union of South Africa who is chairman of the Group for the Study of the Progressive Ideas of South Africa made public a statement on Sept. 4 denouncing the U.S. and south Korean bellicose forces' moves for war against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The war exercises recently staged by the U.S. and south Korean bellicose forces were clearly aimed at threatening the DPRK by force and, at the same time, comprehensively examining and rounding off the operation capability for mounting a preemptive nuclear attack on it, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their exercises for a war of aggression were another grave military provocation to the DPRK and a blatant challenge to all the Korean people and the world progressives who aspire after peace, democracy and reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement urged the U.S. to immediately stop its moves for aggression and war on the Korean Peninsula and make the earliest possible policy switchover to contributing to peace and democracy in the region.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Venezuela
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The work of General Secretary Kim Jong Il "Songun Revolutionary Line Is a Great Revolutionary Line of Our Era and an Ever-Victorious Banner for Our Revolution" was brought out in booklet by the Canta Clara Publishing House of Venezuela. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work published on January 29, Juche 92 (2003) clarifies the idea that the Songun revolutionary leadership and Songun politics of the Workers' Party of Korea are a scientific revolutionary line and political mode which carried forward and developed President Kim Il Sung's idea and line of giving importance to arms and most correctly reflected the requirements of the era and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also deals with the great vitality of the Songun politics and sets forth the tasks to be fulfilled to uphold the Songun leadership.

DPRK Birthday Observed in Cuba
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- An event of laying a floral basket before the portrait of smiling President Kim Il Sung was held at Kim Il Sung Economic Special School in Cuba on Sept. 8 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Juan Jose Leon Vega, first vice-chairman of the Cuban Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification, and other members of the committee, teachers and students of the school, the DPRK ambassador to Cuba and staff members of the DPRK embassy in Havana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants laid a floral basket before the portrait of smiling Kim Il Sung and paid tribute to him.

Celebration Meeting Held in Denmark
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- A celebration meeting was held in Copenhagen on Sept. 2 on the occasions of the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK and the 40th anniversary of the formation of the Denmark-DPRK Friendship Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were the chairman of the Communist Party of Denmark (Marxist-Leninist), the chairman of the Denmark-DPRK Friendship Association and other personages and people. Present there on invitation was a friendship delegation of the DPRK headed by Hong Son Ok, vice-chairwoman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and vice-chairwoman of the Korean Committee for Solidarity with World People. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anders Kristensen, chairman of the Denmark-DPRK Friendship Association, in his speech at the meeting said that the DPRK has covered a glorious path of victory as a genuine people's power for the past six decades since its founding by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people underwent hardships due to the anti-socialist offensive of the U.S. and other imperialist allied forces and the repeated natural disasters in the 1990s, but achieved signal successes in the efforts to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and reunify the country under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, who is successfully carrying forward the cause of the President, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the successes achieved by the DPRK instill great strength and courage into the world progressive people, he reiterated the will to intensify the activities supporting the just cause of the Korean people in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to General Secretary Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

DPRK Praised by Egyptian Figure
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Siham Ahmad Mugahed, chairman of the Egypt-Korea Friendship Association, made public a statement on Sept. 1 on the occasion of the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that the six-decade-long history of the DPRK is a course in which it has defended popular masses-centered socialism and consolidated it as firm as a rock and proved that the dignity and victory of the country and the nation can be guaranteed only when the Songun politics is enforced while building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has preserved the Juche character and national identity in the revolution and construction, regarding the Juche idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung as guidelines and it is widely known as a country independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence, it noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary Kim Jong Il has carried forward and developed the line of giving importance to the military affairs which the President consistently held fast to in the whole period of leading the revolution and construction, thereby establishing a Songun political mode and developing the DPRK into an impregnable socialist bulwark. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has fully demonstrated its majestic appearance thanks to Songun, the statement said, expressing belief that it would always emerge victorious under the banner of Songun.

Kim Jong Il recibe presente del director general de UNESCO
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 12 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio presente que le dirigiera el director general de la Organizacion de las Naciones Unidas para la Educacion, la Ciencia y la Cultura (UNESCO), Matsuura Koichiro, de visita en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El visitante lo entrego el dia 12 a Kim Yong Nam, presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea.

Kim Jong Il recibe carta de participantes en escena conjunta
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 12 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio la carta que le dirigieran el dia 12 los participantes en la escena conjunta televisiva motivada por el 60o aniversario de la fundacion de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 La misiva senala  que le rinden  saludo de sincero agradecimiento al Dirigente Kim Jong Il quien, al adivinar su ardiente sentido de celebrar la significativa fiesta junto con el pueblo coreano, tomo una medida para que ellos participen en la escena conjunta televisiva, la exposicion de los libros que dan a conocer las nobles personalidades de los tres generales del Monte  Paektu  y de las obras que narran los sentimientos de veneracion hacia a estos y otras festividades por 60o aniversario de la fundacion de la RPDC efectuadas en Pyongyang.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Festejar solemnemente  susodicha fiesta junto con el pueblo coreano constituye una sagrada obligacion y deber para nosotros mismos que hemos venido apoyando y respaldando siempre activamente la Corea socialista, baluarte digno de la independencia, la paz y la justicia y redactando los articulos para transmitir los grandes rasgos de los 3 generales del monte Paektu y sus imborrables hazanas, senala la carta y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Opinamos que las presentes festividades sirvieron de significativos motivos para demostrar la aspiracion de la humanidad progresista a transmitir eternamente las inmortales hazanas de los 3 generales del monte Paektu, grandes hombres sin par y a apoyar invariablemente la justa causa del pueblo coreano.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Al igual que en el pasado al encantarnos con los  grandes rasgos de Su Excelencia el Presidente Kim Il Sung hemos venido actuando como adeptos de la gran idea de este y como partidarios activos a la justa causa del pueblo coreano, tambien en el futuro depositaremos en Su Excelencia Kim Jong Il el porvenir de la causa de la independencia de la humanidad y haremos todos nuestros esfuerzos por apoyar la Corea del Songun (priorizacion militar).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 En particular, tomamos nuestra firme determinacion de  de apoyar y respaldar activamente la heroica lucha del pueblo coreano por hacer brillar el centenario del nacimiento de Su Excelencia el Presidente Kim Il Sung como gran jubilo comun de la humanidad nunca visto en la historia y por abrir cueste lo que cueste la gran puerta de la gran potencia prospera.

Atrocidades homicidas de efectivos yanquis en Sur de Corea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 12 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Se cumplen 63 anos desde cuando los uniformados norteamericanos irrumpieron a la tierra del Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante todo el periodo de su presencia en esta parte las tropas invasoras yanquis produjeron numerosos casos de homicidios horrorosos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Desde septiembre de 1945 hasta la fecha, los yanquis acarrearon incontables desgracias y calamidades de toda indole a los habitantes surcoreanos y asesinaron indiscriminadamente a las personas inocentes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En octubre de 1946 los yanquis reprimieron despiadadamente con aviones, tanques y armas quimicas la lucha de los habitantes surcoreanos de todas las localidades contra la "administracion militar" norteamericana y asesinaron a mas de 25 mil personas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante el levantamiento popular del 3 de abril de la isla Jeju contra las elecciones separadas del 10 de mayo que continuo hasta junio de 1949, los uniformados yanquis asesinaron de modo mas cruel a mas de 70 mil de entre 300 mil pobladores en total de la isla. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante los cinco anos de la presencia en Sur de Corea de los militares yanquis llega a mas de un millon el numero de pobladores pacificos asesinados por ellos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tales atrocidades homicidas continuaron tambien en el periodo de la pasada guerra coreana (1950-1953) y el periodo de posguerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Son incontables los homicidios cometidos por los yanquis, entre otros, el "caso de disparo contra una nina de Kunsan" de 1957, el "caso del helicoptero con un cajon en que estaba encerrado un nino de Puphyong" de febrero de 1958, el "caso de asesinato al lenador de Phaju" de 1962, el "caso de tiro a ciegas" de junio de 1981. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los casos de homicidios tienen sus testimonios irrefutables en el levantamiento popular de Kwangju de mayo de 1980. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Segun la orden homicida de los yanquis, la banda de Chun Doo Hwan asesino a mas de 5 mil 700 habitantes de distintos estratos en unos dias despues que se desato el levantamiento popular y dio graves o leves heridas a mas de 14 mil. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El 13 de junio de 2002, en una carretera del distrito de Yangju de la provincia de Kyonggi un carro blindado de los yanquis atropello a plena luz del dia a las alumnas de secundaria Sin Hyo Sun y Sim Mi Son. Los asesinatos y otros actos criminales de las tropas invasoras yanquis ocupantes del Sur de Corea se perpetran sin cesar tambien en el nuevo siglo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  EE.UU. debe poner fin a la historia criminal que acarreo desdichas y sufrimientos a los surcoreanos y retirar sin demora sus tropas del Sur de Corea.
